WEBVTT

00:10:28.160 --> 00:10:30.200
They taught me that it's OK to say 'no'."

00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:33.440
Yeah, I thought, of course it is.

00:10:34.840 --> 00:10:37.080
But many patients don't feel that.

00:10:38.840 --> 00:10:40.976
Compassion and Choices did a study

00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:44.200
where they asked people
about their health care preferences.

00:10:44.760 --> 00:10:48.816
And a lot of people
started their answers with the words

00:10:48.840 --> 00:10:50.280
"Well, if I had a choice ..."

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:53.600
If I had a choice.

00:10:54.880 --> 00:10:56.776
And when I read that "if,"

00:10:56.800 --> 00:10:58.976
I understood better

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:01.856
why one in four people